This paper deals with an online algorithmic problem related to tracking moving objects, which involves designing algorithms to minimize the number of handovers that occur when the object moves outside its assigned region. This problem has applications in various domains such as cellular networks, transportation systems, and surveillance systems. The paper uses techniques from competitive analysis to measure the performance of the algorithms and provides both deterministic and randomized solutions for one and multiple dimensions. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory), cs.IT (Information Theory), cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture), and cs.SY (Systems and Control).
